de.folivora.storage

Class HibernateMongoDBDialect

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.hibernate.ogm.dialect.spi.BaseGridDialect
      • de.folivora.storage.HibernateMongoDBDialect
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, org.hibernate.ogm.dialect.batch.spi.BatchableGridDialect, org.hibernate.ogm.dialect.identity.spi.IdentityColumnAwareGridDialect, org.hibernate.ogm.dialect.optimisticlock.spi.OptimisticLockingAwareGridDialect, org.hibernate.ogm.dialect.query.spi.QueryableGridDialect<org.hibernate.ogm.datastore.mongodb.query.impl.MongoDBQueryDescriptor>, org.hibernate.ogm.dialect.spi.GridDialect, org.hibernate.service.Service

    public class HibernateMongoDBDialect
extends org.hibernate.ogm.dialect.spi.BaseGridDialect
implements org.hibernate.ogm.dialect.query.spi.QueryableGridDialect<org.hibernate.ogm.datastore.mongodb.query.impl.MongoDBQueryDescriptor>, org.hibernate.ogm.dialect.batch.spi.BatchableGridDialect, org.hibernate.ogm.dialect.identity.spi.IdentityColumnAwareGridDialect, org.hibernate.ogm.dialect.optimisticlock.spi.OptimisticLockingAwareGridDialect
    Each Tuple entry is stored as a property in a MongoDB document. Each association is stored in an association document containing three properties: - the association table name (optionally) - the RowKey column names and values - the tuples as an array of elements Associations can be stored as: - one MongoDB collection per association class. The collection name is prefixed. - one MongoDB collection for all associations (the association table name property in then used) - embed the collection info in the owning entity document is planned but not supported at the moment (OGM-177) Collection of embeddable are stored within the owning entity document under the unqualified collection role In MongoDB is possible to batch operations but only for the creation of new documents and only if they don't have invalid characters in the field name. If these conditions are not met, the MongoDB mechanism for batch operations is not going to be used.
    Author:
    Guillaume Scheibel <guillaume.scheibel@gmail.com>, Alan Fitton <alan at eth0.org.uk>, Emmanuel Bernard <emmanuel@hibernate.org>

      • getCollectionName

        private java.lang.String getCollectionName(org.hibernate.ogm.dialect.query.spi.BackendQuery<?> customQuery,
                                           org.hibernate.ogm.datastore.mongodb.query.impl.MongoDBQueryDescriptor queryDescriptor,
                                           org.hibernate.ogm.model.key.spi.EntityKeyMetadata entityKeyMetadata)
        Returns the name of the MongoDB collection to execute the given query against. Will either be retrieved
        • from the given query descriptor (in case the query has been translated from JP-QL or it is a native query using the extended syntax db.<COLLECTION>.<OPERATION>(...)
        • or from the single mapped entity type if it is a native query using the criteria-only syntax
        Parameters:
        customQuery - the original query to execute
        queryDescriptor - descriptor for the query
        entityKeyMetadata - meta-data in case this is a query with exactly one entity return
        Returns:
        the name of the MongoDB collection to execute the given query against
